news.title: Rising land costs, approval delays hit new project launches and property sales
news.para: ​​However, total absorption surpassed new supply by 18%, reducing inventory by 15% during the quarter, according to PropEquity, a data analytics firm. Pune, Hyderabad and Kolkata saw the steepest declines of between 44% to 49% each.

news.title: New home prices in China rise 0.14% in September 2024
news.para: The average price across 100 cities edged up 0.14%, compared with the previous month's 0.11%, showed data released by property researcher China Index Academy.

news.title: PM-UDAY centres to operate seven days a week in Delhi: DDA
news.para: PM-UDAY Scheme is aimed at granting ownership rights to the residents of 1,731 unauthorised colonies in Delhi. The primary objective of this scheme is to provide legal recognition to residents' properties, by conferring ownership rights, the statement said.

news.title: Ahmedabad: SRFDCL eases bidding criteria to attract bidders for riverfront plots
news.para: The SRFDCL issued a request for proposal (RFP) for the sale of development rights for two riverfront plots. No international company showed interest. While the sale drew interest from two Mumbai companies and five from Gujarat, their representatives raised queries regarding the experience criteria and parking.

news.title: Home prices in Australia rise 0.4% in September 2024
news.para: Figures from property consultant CoreLogic, released on Tuesday, showed prices across the nation climbed 0.4% in September, in line with the 0.3% growth seen in July and August.

news.title: Maradu civic body seeks SC approval for new construction at demolition site
news.para: According to reports, SC had recently observed that the case against Maradu apartment complexes, which were found to have violated coastal regulation zone (CRZ) norms, should have been resolved by imposing a heavy fine on flat owners instead of demolition.

news.title: Resident welfare associations in Chennai protest against 6% property tax hike
news.para: In its second annual general body meeting over the weekend, AoRWA passed ten resolutions, emphasizing the need for improved civic infrastructure before implementing tax hikes. "Civic infrastructure and amenities must be provided by the govt on priority, and the tax hike proposal should be put on hold," said AoRWA general secretary J M S Nagarjunan.

news.title: RLDA invites bids for residential development of railway land in Punjabi Bagh, Delhi
news.para: The land parcel covers 46,313.4 sqm (4.63 Ha) and has a reserve price of Rs 1,100 crore, according to an RLDA statement. The parcel will be leased for 99 years, with a maximum permissible Floor Area Ratio (FAR) of 200 on the gross area.

news.title: Lucknow development body streamlines property mutation system to reduce delays
news.para: LDA vice-chairman Prathamesh Kumar said, "The updated system assigns the property section the responsibility of verifying mutation fee payments submitted online, allowing further action to proceed efficiently."

news.title: Only 17 of 33 projects completed in seven years under Patna smart city
news.para: Patna found its name on the Central govt list under the Smart Cities Mission in 2017. Under SCM, the shortlisted cities are entitled to get Rs1,000 crore over a period of five years from the Centre as well as the state govt for the development of selected areas with smart civic facilities.

news.title: Delhi's draft master plan 2041 will be notified soon: Housing minister
news.para: Addressing a press conference on 100 days of the third term of the Modi government, Khattar said there have been some difficulties in preparing the final draft of the MPD, adding that some suggestions that have been received from the public are being considered.

news.title: Registration of properties in Mumbai falls 14% to 9,100 units in September 2024
news.para: As many as 10,694 units were registered in the year-ago period. In August this year, the registration of properties stood at 11,631 units.

news.title: States' contribution mandatory in second phase of PMAY-Urban: Housing minister
news.para: The minister said that the Modi government in its first Cabinet meeting after the Lok Sabha elections this year approved PMAY-U 2.0 for construction of additional one crore houses for eligible urban poor and middle-class families over the next five years.

news.title: Maharashtra approves 255 acres of salt pan land for slum rehabilitation PAP
news.para: The Adani group-controlled Dharavi Redevelopment Project will be responsible for implementing this decision (to develop houses for slum rehabilitation project-affected people), the government stated after Chief Minister Eknath Shinde chaired the cabinet meeting.

news.title: Telangana: ED arrests Sahiti Infratec's MD in Rs 360 crore fraud case
news.para: Boodati Lakshminarayan of Sahiti Infratec Ventures India Pvt. Ltd. (SIVIPL) was taken into custody on Sunday under the provisions of the Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA), it said.

news.title: Kanakia Spaces acquires 3.3 acre redevelopment projects in Mumbai’s Borivali
news.para: Realty developer Kanakia Spaces plans to invest over Rs 1,100 crore for the redevelopment of two large housing societies in Mumbai's Borivali. Spanning 3.3 acres, with a potential value of over Rs 1,500 crore, the project is expected to start in six months and finish in around four years.

news.title: Delhi metro's blue line extension plan from Noida Electronic City to Sahibabad may be revived
news.para: A revised project report submitted by DMRC in Jan had pegged the project's cost at Rs 1,873 crore, up from the estimated Rs 1,517 crore in a 2018 report. The report suggested that 80% of the project cost, which is Rs 1,225.34 crore, should be borne by the state govt through its agencies. UP will foot another Rs 111.8 crore in state taxes.

news.title: Architects and interior designers converged at DesignScape 2024
news.para: The Economic Times DesignScape 2024 conclave and awards held in Taj Lands End, Mumbai on September 26, 2024, witnessed

news.title: Housing society committee members in Maharashtra can respond to complaints online
news.para: Officials from the state cooperation department have said the portal will be upgraded in Oct to enable this two-way communication from Nov.

news.title: Canada's housing affordability crisis may persist for years despite rate cuts
news.para: Even with expectations that Bank of Canada will keep cutting rates in the coming months, the issue of home affordability - which has strangled Prime Minister Justin Trudeau's poll numbers - is unlikely to fade before the next election.
